<TITLE> BFF proposes transfer schedule for Mar 15 to Apr 14 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 29 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) Tuesday proposed a tentative schedule for inter-club footballers' transfers for the professional football league from March 15 to April 14. The proposal came at a meeting between B. League Committee and the clubs' representatives at the BFF House. "The meeting has proposed the tentative schedule of the transfer following the request made by the club representatives at the meeting," said BFF media manager Syed Al Fatah. "The club representatives will let the federation know the exact timeframe of the transfers in seven days after discussing the matter with their high-ups," Fatah said, "The clubs want to rope in the footballers from the Senior Division Football League that is scheduled to complete in the middle of March." On Feb 24, the BFF executive committee meeting asked the B. League Committee to finalise the date for the players' transfers by February after meeting with the club representatives. The footballers on Feb 17 threatened to boycott all types of tournament in their demand for immediate transfers. The meeting also decided to keep the window for the foreign recruits open to allow the clubs to rope in foreign recruits according to their convenient time. Of 11 professional football league clubs, the representatives from Abahani, Mohammedan, Muktijoddha, Sheikh Russel, Arambagh, Rahmatganj and Farashganj were present in the meeting. No representative from Khulna Abahani, Chittagong Abahani and Mohammedan and Dhaka Brothers Union were present. 
